619
00:36:43,023 --> 00:36:48,426
If there's a poison gas feature and the LDs use it everywhere, it could tank your framerate.

620
00:36:48,807 --> 00:36:50,088
Since you can't see the future.

621
00:36:50,648 --> 00:36:54,892
Give LDs a cheap temp version so they can place it in their maps,

622
00:36:55,372 --> 00:37:00,056
and then you can see how much that temp version costs, and now you have a target to aim for.

623
00:37:01,357 --> 00:37:08,083
Oh, and now it should go without saying, level designers, yes, please do follow the metrics.

624
00:37:11,766 --> 00:37:14,228
But when they aren't working, say something.

625
00:37:16,357 --> 00:37:18,338
This may sound all over the place.

626
00:37:19,118 --> 00:37:20,358
So what point am I trying to make?

627
00:37:21,558 --> 00:37:23,119
If your level design and level art teams

628
00:37:23,219 --> 00:37:25,899
are forced to strictly follow the metrics

629
00:37:25,979 --> 00:37:27,900
and have no say in what those metrics are,

630
00:37:28,420 --> 00:37:31,401
you'll wind up with rote, predictable, samey maps.

631
00:37:32,721 --> 00:37:35,262
Metrics must be iterated on like anything else.

632
00:37:35,862 --> 00:37:36,802
And you need wiggle room.

633
00:37:37,402 --> 00:37:39,763
If cover has to be exactly one meter high,

634
00:37:39,783 --> 00:37:43,944
your map will lose believability.

635
00:37:44,144 --> 00:37:44,904
Give them range.

636
00:37:46,370 --> 00:37:48,151
It's a balanced give and take.

637
00:37:48,751 --> 00:37:50,871
Sometimes a metric must be strictly followed,

638
00:37:50,891 --> 00:37:53,112
know when to give and know when to hold firm.

639
00:37:54,492 --> 00:37:56,893
If you set up processes around the idea

640
00:37:56,933 --> 00:37:58,413
that metrics will be flexible,

641
00:37:58,593 --> 00:38:01,394
everything will be easier and ready to change.

642
00:38:02,254 --> 00:38:05,214
But most of all, if the metrics aren't working

643
00:38:05,935 --> 00:38:08,255
or too restrictive, you have to speak up.

644
00:38:08,835 --> 00:38:10,996
And when LDs speak up, please listen.

645
00:38:12,876 --> 00:38:14,637
Challenge six, pivots happen.

